result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica L. Helminiak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jessica L. Helminiak in court with attorney Gary J. Kryshak. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard today are 16CM156 & 16CM486.

9:55 a.m.  Court calls the case and states the appearances.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
16CM156:
Count 1 - No contest
Count 2 - DRI

16CM486:
Count 1 - No contest
Count 2 - No contest 

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).
State has complied with victim notification; no victim appears in Court today (record reflects no victim appears today).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty on Count 1 of 16CM156 and Count 2 is DRI and guilty on Count 1 & 2 of 16CM486.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Kryshak makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant does not wish to make a statement prior to sentencing.

BY THE COURT:
16CM156:
Count 1 -
Pay $100 fine plus costs
Pay DNA surcharge
Pay within 60 days or you will need to set up a payment plan today with the Clerk of Court's Office.

Count 2 - DRI

16CM486:
Count 1 -
Impose/Stay 40 day jail sentence - with huber priviliges for work or any counseling she may be involved in

**Conditions of Probation:
Pay costs
Pay DNA surcharge
Participate in any counseling or assessments as deemed appropriate and recommended by the agent.
Submit a DNA sample, if not already done so


Count 2 -
Impose/Stay 90 day jail sentence to be consective to Count 1 - with huber priviliges for work or any counseling she may be involved in
First 45 in jail and the second 45 on GPS electronic home monitor if approved by jail administration and risk assessment
Placed on Probation for 18 months -
**Conditions of Probation:
Pay costs
Pay DNA surcharge
Comply with conditions as stated in Count 1

20 days to appeal
